Drop the vestigial X11 includes from shell-app-usage.c.

gnome-shell 50 includes <X11/Xlib.h> and <X11/Xatom.h> unconditionally in
src/shell-app-usage.c, but the file uses no X11 symbols -- the includes are
left-over cruft. The X11 headers are only wired into the build when mutter
reports have_xwayland, and our mutter is Wayland-only, so the file fails to
compile. Remove the dead includes.

--- a/src/shell-app-usage.c
+++ b/src/shell-app-usage.c
@@ -5,8 +5,6 @@
 #include <string.h>
 #include <stdlib.h>

-#include <X11/Xlib.h>
-#include <X11/Xatom.h>
 #include <glib.h>
 #include <gio/gio.h>
 #include <meta/display.h>
